
== Stock Vocabulary ==
* VAMA (volume adjust moving average): A metric to measure market action by taking into account volume (instead of time) and price. Volume represents overall trading activity and takes into account the contribution of closing prices; it does not just average closing price over a period of time.
* Sharpe Ratio: A measure that indicates the average return minus the risk free return divided by the standard deviation. (Avg(x) - rfr(x))/std(x)
